== Application Startup ==

group Main()
    Main->Main: use flag.String() and define the name env for it and provide the default name as dev and provide description message as Environment(dev,qc,uat,prod)
    activate Main
    Main->Main: then assign it to the variable env
    Main->Main: use flag.Parse() which visit the command line terminal and check the input for example go run main.go env=dev like that it parsing it and assign it to the env
    Main->Server: declare a variable app and err and call the InitializeApp function and pass the env to it
    group InitializeApp()
        activate Server
        Server->Config: create a variable cfg and err and call the function LoadConfig() and pass the service name booking-service and the env to it
        group LoadConfig()
            activate Config
                Config->Config: provide the root path of the env file based on the env for example if dev is passed the developer env should be get like that
                alt if godotenv.Load() envFile
                    alt if not exists
                        Config->Config: if envFile is unable to load which means os.IsNotExist(err) then through "env file isnt present continuing without env file"
                    else
                        Config->Config: if any other error is thrown then throw like failed to load envfile like that and return it
                    end
                end
                Config->Config:create a variable config and then use the struct Config{} which have Port, databaseurl,projectroot and the baseurl and define field here by calling the getEnv() function and pass the key value within it for example "PORT",DATABASE_URL,PROJECT_ROOT, and BASE_URL
                group getEnv()
                    alt if the value is not nil
                        Config->Config: use Getenv() and pass the key to it and get the value of each caller if not unable to get then return empty string
                    end
                end
                Config-->Server: return the config and also the nil to the caller
            deactivate Config
        end
        Server -> Logger: NewLogger(LogConfig{Level, LogDir, FileName, ServiceName})
        group NewLogger()
            activate Logger
                Logger -> Logger: os.MkdirAll(logDir)
                Logger -> Logger: os.OpenFile(filePath)
                Logger -> Logger: zap.New(core, AddCaller)
                Logger --> Server: *Logger
            deactivate Logger
        end
        Server->Server: create a variable dbService and use the &database.DBService{}
        Server -> DB:create a variables db and err and call EstablishConnection()function and pass the cfg.DatabaseURL to it
        group EstablishConnection()
            activate DB
            DB->DB: declare a variable dialector with type gorm.Dialector this variable stores which database driver should be used\nfor example sqlite or sqlserver
            alt if strings.HasPrefix()
                DB->DB: use strings.HasPrefix() and check whether the dbURL starts with sqlite:// example sqlite://test.db
                DB->DB: create a variable dbPath and use strings.TrimPrefix() to remove sqlite:// from the URL\nexample sqlite://test.db becomes test.db
                DB->DB: assign sqlite.Open(dbPath) into dialector this prepares the sqlite driver with the database file path
            else if strings.HasPrefix()
                DB->DB: check whether the dbURL starts with sqlserver:// example sqlserver://localhost:1433
                DB->DB: assign sqlserver.Open(dbURL) into dialector\nthis prepares the sqlserver database driver using the provided URL
            else
                DB->DB: if no known prefix is matched then default to sqlserver.Open(dbURL)
                DB->DB: assign sqlserver.Open(dbURL) into dialector this acts as the fallback database driver
            end
            DB->DB: create variables db and err and call gorm.Open() pass the dialector and &gorm.Config{} gorm.Open() establishes the GORM database connection
            alt if err != nil
                DB-->Server: return nil and err this means the database connection creation failed
            end
            DB->DB: create variables sqlDB and err and call db.DB() this converts the GORM database instance into native sql.DB object
            alt if err != nil
                DB-->Server: return nil and err this means unable to extract the native sql.DB instance
            end
            DB->DB: call sqlDB.Ping() Ping() checks whether the database is reachable and alive
            alt if err := sqlDB.Ping(); err != nil
                DB-->Server: return nil and err this means the database server is unreachable or connection failed
            end
            DB->DB: create and return &Db{} assign Gorm field with db assign SqlDb field with sqlDB
            DB-->Server: return &Db{Gorm: db, SqlDb: sqlDB}, nil successful database connection object is returned
           
        end
        Server->DB: create a variable err and call database.AutoMigrate() and pass the db and logger to it
        group AutoMigrate()
            DB->DB: create a variable err and use db.Gorm.AutoMigrate() then add models like Rooms,Customers,Bookings and Booking_rooms/ to it
            alt if err is not nil
                DB->Server: return err to the server shows failed to run migrations and shows internal server 500 to it
            end
            DB-->Server: return nil to the server caller function
        end
        alt if migration failed
            DB-->Server: if unable to connect the db automigrate then through the error and return nil and err
            deactivate DB
            Server-->Main: throw internal server error 500
            Main-->Client:upwards and forwards the error to the client and raise the internal server error 500
        end
        Server->Server: create a variable router and assign mux.NewRouter() to it to use gorrilla mux
        Server->Router: use handlers and call the SetUpRoutes functions in the routes and pass this above router, db, logger and cfg to it
        activate Router
        group SetupRoutes()
            Router->Router: create a variable bookRepo and use repostiory and initialize its NewBookRepository with passing db and logger to it
            Router->Router: create a variable bookService and use services and injects the bookRepo and logger to the NewBookService
            Router->Router: create a variable bookHandler and use NewBookHandler and inject the bookService and logger to it
            Router->Router: create a variable api and setup the router path prefix as "book/api/v1"
            Router->Router: and use api.HandleFunc() and the endpoint as cancelling and use the bookHandler.BookRoom and define its method as post
            Router->Router: then again use the same endpoint and register the other functions like GetRooms and CancelRoom to it with the GET method and PATCH method
            deactivate Router
        end
        Server-->Main: assign the filed logger,router,cfg,dbservice with respective field of the Application struct and return it to the main
        alt if recive an err
            Main-->Client: raise standardize error and throw like failed to initialize the app then close the terminal by providing the os.Exit as 1
        end
        Main->Server: call the server.RunServer() and pass the app to it
        alt if err is not nil
            Main-->Client: raise the message like failed to start the server
            deactivate Main
        end
        group GetCorsOptions()
            Server->Server: return the cors options with allowedOrigins, allowed methods and allowedheaders to it
        end
        group RunServer()
            Server->Server: create a variable corsOpts and assign the GetCorsOptions() functions to it
            Server->Server: create a variable handler and bind the corsOpts with the Handler and app.router tell the server like first entering corsmiddleware then register routes and go to handlers
            Server->Server: use http.ListenAndServe() and pass the port number eg: 8080 by using app.config.Port and assign the handler here
        end
        deactivate Server
    end
end

== Get room request ==
activate Client
Client -> Handler: GET /api/v1/bookings
activate Handler
group GetRoom()
Handler -> Handler: use the function GetRooms(w,r)
activate Logger
Handler -> Logger: While processing the booking request, the Handler records a log message stating that a room is being cancelled.Info("Recieved request to cancel room")
Handler -> Handler : Extracts path parameters from the incoming HTTP request using mux.Vars(r)
Handler -> Handler : Extracts bookingID from the path parameters map (vars) obtained from the request URL and assigns them to local variables for further processing.
alt if bookingID is empty
    Handler -> Utils: Create error response (400, "booking_id is required", validation error details)
    Utils -> Client: Forward HTTP 400 error response to the client
    note over Client
    {
        "code": 400,
        "status": "error",
        "message": "booking_id is required",
        "data": null,
        "errors": [
            {
                "field": "bookingID",
                "message": "missing in path",
                "code": "BAD_REQUEST"
            }
        ]
    }
    end note
end
Handler -> Service: call GetRoomByBookingID(ctx,bookingID)
group Service-GetRoomByBookingID
Service -> Repo: Defines the GetRoomByBookingID(ctx, bookingID) method in the repository, where `ctx` is used to manage the request lifecycle, `bookingID` is used to identify the booking record, and it returns `room` (the associated room details) along with `dtoErr` (error details if any issue occurs during the database operation)
group Repo-GetRoomByBookingID
Repo -> Repo: Declares a variable `booking` of type models.Booking to store the booking record fetched from the database
Repo ->  DB: Executes a query using `bookingID` and active status to fetch the booking record from the Booking table and stores the result in `booking`
note over DB
r.db.Gorm.WithContext(ctx).
Where("uuid = ? AND is_active = ?", bookingID, true).
First(&booking).Error
end note

alt if room record is not found or query fails (err != nil)
  Repo -> Logger: Logs an error message "GetRoomByBookingID room lookup failed" along with detailed error information for debugging purposes
   Repo -> Service: Returns a structured error response (room: nil, field: "room_id", message: "room not found", code: "NOT_FOUND")
else 
  Repo -> Service: Proceeds with the retrieved room data stored in `room` and continues execution without any error (dtoErr = nil)
  deactivate Repo
  end

alt if error is present (dtoErr != nil)
   Service -> Logger: Logs an error message "GetRoomByBookingID failed" along with the bookingID and detailed error message from dtoErr for tracking and debugging
   deactivate Logger
   Service -> Handler: Creates a structured error response (code: 500, message: "failed to fetch room by booking ID", errors: [dtoErr])
   Handler-> Utils: Returns the error APIResponse back to the handler
   Utils -> Client:
   note over Client
     {
                    code:500,
                    status:"error",
                    message:"Internal server error booking room is failed",
                    data:None,
                    error:{"type": "HandlerException", "details": str(e)},
                    request_id:request_id,
                    timestamp: timestamp,
                }
   end note
else
Service -> Handler: Creates a structured success response with status code 200, message "Room fetched successfully", and includes room details such as RoomType, Capacity, and Price in the response data
deactivate Service
Handler -> Utils: Returns the response back to the handler
deactivate Utils
Utils -> Client:
  note over Client
  {
    "code": 200,
    "status": "success",
    "message": "Booking details retrieved successfully",
    "data": {
      "booking_id": 205,
      "customer_name": "Kirthika",
      "capacity": 3,
      "room_type": "AC",
      "floor": 4,
      "room_name": "maya",
      "price": 450
    },
    "error": null,
    "request_id": "e137e7b1-6b6c-4d5a-993b-b6b49b9e0a52"
}
   end note
   deactivate Handler
end
   deactivate Client
  end
  end
